      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@AvijitBarua The process id (pid) of the java programm bound to this port is 106872. Every Java program that you launch presents itself as the program java (it is the java virtual machine that runs your compiled code). So yes, you could exit or kill this java program, if it is not some critical (system) tool, but your own program; have a look in a task manager like <code>htop</code>. Maybe you try to bind to a port used by a valid program that should not be killed."
    } ],
