    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you know what port the process is running you can type: \n<code>lsof -i:&lt;port&gt;</code>. </p>\n\n<p>For instance, <code>lsof -i:8080</code>, to list the process (pid) running on port 8080. </p>\n\n<p>Then kill the process with <code>kill &lt;pid&gt;</code></p>\n"
