      "creation_date" : 1593426404,
      "post_id" : 26147631,
      "comment_id" : 110767435,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "For me (using Windows 10) <code>find</code> didn&#39;t work but <code>findstr</code> did. To avoid false positives it also helps to prepend a colon, e.g. <code>netstat -ano | findstr :8080</code>. Having done this - let&#39;s say it returned a PID of 1234 - if you then want to look up the name of this process this can be done via <code>tasklist &#47;fi &quot;pid eq 1234</code>&quot;."
    } ],
