    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4203782,
      "reputation" : 1976,
      "user_id" : 3443247,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 100,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/RYFZY.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Sufiyan Ansari",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3443247/sufiyan-ansari"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 37,
    "last_activity_date" : 1529915734,
    "creation_date" : 1529915734,
    "answer_id" : 51019260,
    "question_id" : 12737293,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><strong>(Windows Only)</strong></p>\n\n<p>To kill a process you first need to find the Process Id (pid)</p>\n\n<p>By running the command :</p>\n\n<pre><code>netstat -ano | findstr :yourPortNumber\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/ue3dJ.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/ue3dJ.png\" alt=\"As shown in picture below\"></a></p>\n\n<p>You will get your Process Id (PID), Now to kill the same process run this command:</p>\n\n<pre><code>taskkill /pid yourid /f\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/G2gKF.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/G2gKF.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7416245,
      "reputation" : 727,
      "user_id" : 5641961,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/8cCtE.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Machhindra Neupane",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5641961/machhindra-neupane"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1541055060,
    "last_edit_date" : 1541055060,
    "creation_date" : 1541054622,
    "answer_id" : 53096349,
    "question_id" : 12737293,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You need to close your port \nif you are a linux user then type</p>\n\n<pre><code>fuser -k 8080/tcp\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 14282929,
      "reputation" : 353,
      "user_id" : 10317086,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/735ed8c1abf1a1f7b907b78d9594303c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "EnGoPy",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10317086/engopy"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1571135119,
    "creation_date" : 1571135119,
    "answer_id" : 58392490,
    "question_id" : 12737293,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In my case Tomcat was running in a background. I've installed it as a external servlet while using Eclipse.\nWith a Spring Boot in Intellij it has it own server but cannot start while it's already occupied.<br>\nIn my case Tomcat starts automatically I turn on my OS, that is why I need to shut down him manualy:<br></p>\n\n<pre><code>$ sudo service tomcat stop\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>of course \"tomcat\" depends what version of tomcat you are using. \n<br>\nHope it might help to someone.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3691447,
      "reputation" : 7145,
      "user_id" : 3073945,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 90,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Dig4I.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Md. Sajedul Karim",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3073945/md-sajedul-karim"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 23,
    "last_activity_date" : 1646044218,
    "last_edit_date" : 1646044218,
    "creation_date" : 1588147578,
    "answer_id" : 61497005,
    "question_id" : 12737293,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><strong>For windows</strong> :</p>\n<ol>\n<li><p><strong>Find the process id</strong></p>\n<p>netstat -nao | find &quot;8080&quot;</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>It will show you the process ID as a number.</p>\n<p><strong>Example</strong>:</p>\n<pre><code>TCP    0.0.0.0:8080           0.0.0.0:0              LISTENING       18856\n</code></pre>\n<p>Here <strong>18856</strong> is the process ID</p>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li><p><strong>Kill that process</strong></p>\n<p>taskkill /PID  18856 /F</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>Output</strong> : SUCCESS: The process with PID 18856 has been terminated.</p>\n<p>Here using taskkill you are killing the process ID:18856</p>\n<p><strong>For linux/Mac</strong>:</p>\n<pre><code>sudo kill -9 $(sudo lsof -t -i:8080)\n</code></pre>\n<p>Here you find the process by port <strong>8080</strong> using <code>sudo lsof -t -i:8080</code> and killing it by sudo kill command</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5995486,
      "reputation" : 684,
      "user_id" : 4710245,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-4GnvLw0CYEU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABw/iWcKuuXeQcs/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Anthony Pi&#241;ero",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4710245/anthony-pi%c3%b1ero"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1601334484,
    "creation_date" : 1601334484,
    "answer_id" : 64110758,
    "question_id" : 12737293,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can close every Java Process and start again your app:</p>\n<pre><code>taskkill /F /IM java.exe\n</code></pre>\n<p>start your app again...</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7916122,
      "reputation" : 91,
      "user_id" : 5978490,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-CGpGYvGJtwY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAANc/ekgNLwfRopw/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Shobana T",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5978490/shobana-t"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1629187627,
    "last_edit_date" : 1629187627,
    "creation_date" : 1629187138,
    "answer_id" : 68813654,
    "question_id" : 12737293,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>This BindException would come when another process is already running in the specified port(8080).</p>\n<p>You can use anyone of the following approach.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><p><strong>Change the server port:</strong> If you are using Tomcat server and IntelliJ IDE, you can configure the server port by configuring the tomcat server</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/pFonb.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/pFonb.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>or</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Go to tomcat&gt;conf folder</li>\n<li>Edit server.xml</li>\n<li>Search &quot;Connector port&quot;</li>\n<li>Replace &quot;8080&quot; by your port number</li>\n<li>Restart tomcat server.</li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li><strong>Kill the existing running process in that port and start the server.</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>For Linux/Mac</strong></p>\n<pre><code>sudo kill -9 $(sudo lsof -t -i:8080)\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>For Windows</strong></p>\n<pre><code>netstat -ano | findstr :8080\ntaskkill /PID typeyourPIDhere /F \n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> (/F forcefully terminates the process)</p>\n</blockquote>\n"
  }, {
